DATA STOCK MARKET / DATA EXCHANGE v1.0

Timestamp Anchor — Canonical Concept Entry

Core Premise

People allocate their data the same way they allocate capital.

Instead of companies extracting data for free, individuals invest their data into entities (companies, models, research pools) and receive proportional upside from the value it generates.

Your data should earn like your money does.

⸻

System Definition

User = Data Capital Holder

Each user possesses:
	•	Data streams (behavioral, health, transactional, etc.)
	•	Consent controls (how data can be used)
	•	Allocation choices (where data is deployed)
	•	Yield expectations (what they receive back)

⸻

Company = Data Capital Consumer

Each company defines:
	•	Data demand profile (what they need)
	•	Use-case constraints (training, ads, research, etc.)
	•	Compensation model (rev share, payouts, perks)
	•	Trust/reputation score

⸻

Platform = Exchange Layer

The system acts as:
	•	Matching engine (data ↔ demand)
	•	Consent enforcement layer
	•	Attribution + valuation engine
	•	Payout router

⸻

Core Objects

1. Data Wallet
	•	Unified interface for user data streams
	•	Permission + access control center
	•	Portable identity layer

⸻

2. Data Portfolio
	•	Where users allocate their data
	•	Structured like an investment portfolio:
	•	AI Training
	•	Healthcare
