3. Data Tickers

Each entity/pool has:
	•	Demand score
	•	Trust score
	•	Historical yield
	•	Privacy level
	•	Lock-up constraints
	•	Usage permissions

⸻

4. Data Funds (Primary Wedge)

Instead of raw trading:

Users invest into:
	•	AI Training Fund
	•	Fitness / Health Fund
	•	Shopper Behavior Fund
	•	Autonomous Systems Fund
	•	Local Economy Fund

Funds aggregate data → companies pay → users receive yield

⸻

5. Consent Derivatives

Users define how data is used:
	•	Training only
	•	Insights only
	•	Ads allowed / disallowed
	•	No resale
	•	Anonymized only
	•	Exclusive (premium)
	•	Revocable

Consent becomes a programmable asset

⸻

6. Yield Streams

Users earn via:
	•	Cash payouts
	•	Discounts
	•	Tokens / credits
	•	Revenue share
	•	Access to premium services

⸻

Valuation Engine (Moat Layer)

Data is not equal.

Value is calculated via:
	•	Rarity
	•	Quality
	•	Recency
	•	Verified outcomes
	•	Impact on downstream models
	•	Exclusivity
	•	Consistency over time

→ System estimates marginal contribution of data to value creation

This = the “price discovery engine” of the data economy

